---
import GradientText from '../ui/GradientText.astro';
---

<section class="py-16 lg:py-24" data-animate="fade-in-from-bottom">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
    <GradientText tag="h2" class="page-subtitle text-center mb-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      Our Pieces are hand made by illustrious master craftsmen of Vietri sul Mare,
      where the ceramics tradition was born.
    </GradientText>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The vibrant colours of our ceramics are inspired by the nature of the Amalfi Coast:
          the deep blue of the Tyrrhenian Sea, the lush green of the terraced gardens,
          the warm red and orange of Mediterranean sunsets, and the bright yellow of the
          famous Amalfi lemons. Each colour is carefully mixed and applied by hand,
          following recipes passed down through generations.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Our master craftsmen use ancient techniques that date back centuries: hand-forging
          each piece on the potter's wheel, applying multiple layers of glaze, and painting
          intricate designs with fine brushes. Every ceramic piece that leaves our shop
          carries the unmistakable mark of genuine Italian craftsmanship — no two pieces
          are exactly alike.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
